cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with stochastic optimization problems that arise in machine learning, specifically in empirical risk minimization settings such as Lasso, Ridge Regression, and Logistic Regression. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also presents a new algorithm based on stochastic gradient descent with variance reduction, which involves numerical optimization techniques, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) another likely category. The paper also includes experiments to support the theory, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization problems that arise in various machine learning tasks, such as image classification, which could make cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) possible categories as well.
